# FastAPI Backend Design Rules

## Response Shape
- ALL API responses must follow the standardized shape:
```python
{
    "data": {...},  # Contains the actual response data
    "error": None   # Contains error info when applicable, otherwise null
}
```
- Use Pydantic models for consistent response typing:
```python
class StandardResponse(BaseModel):
    data: Optional[Any] = None
    error: Optional[str] = None
```

## File Structure
```
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app initialization
│   ├── core/
│   │   ├── config.py        # Settings and configuration
│   │   ├── security.py      # Auth utilities (JWT, bcrypt)
│   │   └── database.py      # Database connection
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │   ├── deps.py          # Dependency injection functions
│   │   └── v1/
│   │       ├── __init__.py
│   │       ├── router.py    # Main API router
│   │       └── endpoints/
│   │           ├── auth.py
│   │           ├── lessons.py
│   │           ├── progress.py
│   │           └── tutor.py
│   ├── models/              # Pydantic models
│   │   ├── __init__.py
